<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-009-263 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 500 718</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Nov 19 1991 v5 n40 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Quantum moves into removable-storage market. (introduces PassportXL line of hard disk drives) (Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Quantum Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    QNTM.andO;Product:   Quantum Passport XL (Removable hard disk drive) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionRemovable DiskHard Disk.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Henry NorrandM;Milpitas, Calif.andP;  -- Quantum Corp. this week will jump into theremovable-storage market with a new line of removable-mechanism systems forthe Mac as well as IBM PCs and compatibles.andM;The Passport XL line, to be offered both on the Quantum label and throughthird-party integrators, will include drives with base capacities of 52, 105,120 and 240 Mbytes.andP;  Based on Quantum's low-profile 3.5-inch ProDrive LPSline, the drives have average seek times of 17 to 18 seconds and sustainedtransfer rates of 1.4 Mbytes per second.andP;  They are protected againstnon-operating shocks of 150 G's or more and carry MTBF (mean time betweenfailure) ratings of 250,000 hours.andM;The 52- and 105-Mbyte models are slated to ship in January, with the largercapacities expected by March.andP;  The company will offer internal versions forthe Quadra 900 and PCs, as well as external systems.andP;  A carrying case andSilverlining, the disk utility package from Quantum's La Cie Ltd. subsidiary,will be bundled with each unit.andM;In the Quantum system the entire head-disk assembly can be ejected, incontrast to removable-media drives such as those from SyQuest Technology andIomega Inc., where only relatively inexpensive cartridges containing therecording media are removable.andM;The drive units weigh 1.9 pounds and measure 1.3 by 4.9 by 7.5 inches.andO;Quantum said it has modified the drive's controllers to make it possible toeject the mechanisms in software (by dragging to the Trash, for example) andto insert a module of different capacity without restarting.andM;Because removable-drive technology offers a straightforward approach tosecurity, Quantum said it will market the new line particularly at users whowant an easy way to keep data confidential, such as doctors, attorneys andpersonnel-department officials, as well as users in government and defenseindustries.andP;  In addition, by offering extra chasses, the company hopes toattract customers who want to carry their work environment between offices orbetween home and office.andM;Quantum representatives said, however, that because of the relatively highcost of extra Passport XL drive modules, its approach might not be anattractive alternative for buyers who now use SyQuest or Iomega Bernoullidrives for backup or to transfer large files between sites.andM;Quantum Corp. is at 500 McCarthy Blvd., Milpitas, Calif.andP;  95035.andP;  Phone (408)894-4000 or (800) 624-5545; fax (408) 894-3205.andO;</TEXT></DOC>